{
  "text": "Interestingly, we also found no association of ACE gene polymorphism with the risk of susceptibility to COPD or COPD with PH in Caucasians, whereas the D allele or DD genotype increased the risk of susceptibility to COPD and COPD with PH in Asians. Our finding is in accord with the studies of Li et al [CITATION_1] and Kanazawa et al, [CITATION_2] respectively. Further, the sample size used for meta-analysis in our study is larger than that used in Li et al's study. [CITATION_3] Moreover, we performed the subgroup analysis and the sensitivity analysis, and hence, our results are more reliable. Finally, we analyzed the association of ACE polymorphism and COPD with PH.",
  "citation_candidates": [
